title: 1976 Benson & Hedges Cup
text:
The 1976 Benson & Hedges Cup was the fifth competing of cricket’s <a href="Benson%20%26amp%3B%20Hedges%20Cup">Benson & Hedges Cup</a>. The competition was won by <a href="Kent%20County%20Cricket%20Club">Kent County Cricket Club</a>. Compared with <a href="1975%20Benson%20%26amp%3B%20Hedges%20Cup">the previous year</a>, the groups were no longer organised on a regional basis, and the <a href="Minor%20counties%20of%20English%20and%20Welsh%20cricket">minor counties</a> were divided east-west rather than north-south.
